Elizabeth Kemp https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elizabeth_Kemp 0 Elizabeth Kemp (November 5, 1951 – September 1, 2017) was an American actress and acting coach. She began her career appearing in the television series Love of Life in 1973, after having studied at the American Academy of Dramatic Arts and at the Actors Studio under Lee Strasberg. She went on to become an acting coach and faculty member of the Actors Studio Drama School at Pace University.
